<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Dictionary · Quiz</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -IST suffix creates person nouns — the practitioner, believer, or specialist form of a concept. PHYSICIST, CYCLIST, OPTIMIST — these words are Scrabble gold because they're 7-9 letters naturally, landing them squarely in bingo territory. At 3 base points (I1+S1+T1) the suffix is cheap to add but builds long, high-scoring words.</p>

<p>Combined with the -ISM pattern, learning -IST words gives you a powerful two-suffix vocabulary system from a single set of roots.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -IST Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
